parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to failure to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: stays on for an extended period
or flashes; the airbag system fails to deploy in an accident; the seat belt cannot be unlatched when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the seat belt system can lead to failure to restrain the occupant in an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The seat belt cannot be unlatched when the brake pedal is pressed; the seat belt fails to restrain the occupant in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS (Supplemental Restraint System) can lead to failure to deploy airbags in an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The SRS light comes on after adjusting the seat; the airbag system fails to deploy in an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the driver's seat can cause the seat to move unexpectedly, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat slides back and forth while driving
the driver's seat moves forward when the brakes are applied
the seat heater malfunctions and causes burns or damage to the seat or clothing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The incorrectly machined guide sleeve in the manual transmission can cause the transmission to jump out of gear without warning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
causing the vehicle to lose power and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential unit can cause the rear tire to stop spinning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The rear tire stops spinning while traveling at moderate speeds
causing the vehicle to lose traction and potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden locking of the front passenger seatbelt while the vehicle is in motion can cause distractions, increase the risk of accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The front passenger seatbelt locks up while the vehicle is in motion
the seatbelt retracts but does not release
